section.section:
Money may not be paid under this subsection until the defendant:
has been found guilty;
has pleaded nolo contendere;
has been placed on probation before judgment; or
has been found not criminally responsible for criminal conduct under § 3-109 of this article.

text.section:
Except as provided in subsection (f) of this section, the Attorney General shall pay over to the defendant all of the money from the escrow account if:
the charges against the defendant are dismissed;
a nolle prosequi is entered;
the defendant is acquitted;
the defendant is found to be incompetent to stand trial under § 3-106 of this article and at least 5 years have passed since that finding without a further disposition of the charge; or
the charges against the defendant are placed on the stet docket, and at least 3 years have passed.
